description.809.0: Charles and Ray Eames adapted molding techniques developed during World War II to mass produce this classic design. Available in side and armchair versions, Today's Molded Plastic Chairs are true to the originals and are fully authentic, with updated materials to meet environmental requirements.     Charles and Ray Eames, always interested in new materials, saw in plastic the chance to form organic seat shells that conform to the body's shape. The enduring forms and quality construction make the Molded Plastic Chairs - available here with a classic Eames wire base - comfortable, durable performers.    The Design:      New materials, especially those that held promise for doing more with less, fascinated Charles and Ray Eames throughout their careers. Their fascination led to inventive modern furniture, such as the Molded Plastic Chair. Designed in 1948, it was the first plastic chair to be mass produced, The current models look exactly the same as the originals. They remain unupholstered, in keeping with the Eameses requirement that materials be expressed honestly and unselfconsciously. In fact, these were the first one-piece plastic chairs to be left uncovered    At the same time, the chairs are better than ever. For example, the shell is now manufactured using more environmentally friendly, high-impact plastic

description.864.0: Philippe Starck and Eugeni Quitllet pay homage to three different midcentury modern masters in one sleek, versatile indoor-outdoor seat. The Masters Chair (2010) weaves together the back silhouettes of Jacobsen's Series 7Chair, the Eameses' Molded Plastic Chair and Saarinen's Tulip Armchair to create something entirely new. Lightweight and durable, the Masters Chair has a wide, roomy seat, while the back rest allows you to feel supported on a historic level as it echoes the lines of the very first ergonomic innovators. The iconoclastic Starck has been working with Kartell since the 1980s, mixing the company's desire to develop eco-friendly, contemporary plastic furniture with the designer's unmistakably edgy and innovative style. Stackable up to four high. Made in Italy. The Masters chair is a powerful tribute to the three symbolic chairs, re-read and re-interpreted by the creative genius of Starck. The "Series 7" by Arne Jacobsen, the "Tulip Armchair" by Eero Saarinen and the "Eiffel Chair" by Charles Eames interweave their unmistakable silhouettes into a sinuous hybrid giving life to a fusion of original and engaging styles. On its four slim legs, the Masters chair is roomy and comfy. The special finish on the chair makes it feel sensual and velvety to the touch. The back of the chair is naturally its most distinctive feature, characterised by the fullness and empty spaces created by the curvaceous criss-crossing lines of three different backs which descend to meet at the seat edge. The Masters is light, practical and can be stacked and used outdoors as well. The Masters chair was honoured with the prestigious "2010 Good Design Award" presented by the Chicago Athenaeum - Museum of Architecture and Design.

description.95.0: The shape of the chairs conforms to your body, providing comfort and maximum style. From the grand sweep of the arms to the traditional nail-head accent, this chair is the ultimate in sophistication.
description.952.0: With its comfortable plush seating and padded back and armrests, you won't mind having some company for a relaxing time in the modern Jackson Dining chair. This stylish piece of furniture will look great in your home!
description.953.0: The Elite features a graceful flower hand stitched into the leather back for a unique and creative touch on an already aristocratic piece.
description.955.0: Add some wild flair to your decor with these elegant damask parson chairs. The chairs are not only fashionable, they also have a contoured back and a comfortable seating cushion.
description.956.0: Modern yet casual, the soft leather seat and gently curved back add an interesting note to a chair equally at home in a contemporary, transitional or global decor.
description.957.0: Exquisitely gorgeous, the Hokku Designs Zoie Velvet Parsons Chair (Set of 2) changes the way you look at your home interiors. The cozy seat and backrest are covered in rich espresso upholstery and offer lots of comfort for many hours. This chair comes with impressive ergonomics, which offer a relaxing sitting posture. The felt foot pads prevent scratches on the floor and ensure that the chair stands firmly at all times. The Zoie Velvet Parsons Chair (Set of 2) from Hokku Designs can be placed even in commercial areas like restaurants, lounges and bars.
description.958.0: The Monaco Chair is a chair fit for royals. With it's tall wide backrest it will provide comfort and support for everyone. You can make sure to match it to your current style. Make The Monaco your next throne!
description.959.0: The Royal is not your everyday dining chair. Lush, handstitched cream leather and a dark finished solid beechwood construction provide an eye pleasing contrast of colors and textures.
description.96.0: Sophisticated in its simplicity, the Havre collection will be the center of attention in your dining room. The wood framed chairs feature a flared design inset.
description.961.0: These dining chairs are finished in pu with a comfortable padding and a Sonoma paper back finish. The chrome frame adds the perfect finishing touch to these contemporary dining chairs
description.963.0: What a beautifully crafted upholstered parsons chair. The Itaki chair is upholstered in unique fabric that gives this chair a very distinct look for any room in the home. This chair will work well with any table and can be used in the den, living room, or entry way in the home. The decorative fabric will add to your designer in the home. This classic chair with a trendy flair will fit perfectly in the home and will give that room the added touch you have been looking for!
description.964.0: Enhance the look of your home interiors with the Linon Titian Side Chair. Simplistic lines and slanting slats on the backrest dominate the chair’s overall design. The wide seat is delicately scooped out and offers optimum comfort for long hours. You can place this chair in your dining room beside your table or kitchen island. With an ISTA 3A certification, this chair comes with decent safety for it during transit. Crafted from manufactured wood, the Titian Side Chair from Linon comes with quality that will last for a very long time. This chair can be kept spick and span by wiping it with a damp cloth.
description.966.0: Charles and Ray Eames adapted molding techniques developed during World War II to mass produce this classic design. Today's Molded Plastic Chairs are true to the originals and are fully authentic, with updated materials to meet environmental requirements. Charles and Ray Eames, always interested in new materials, saw in plastic the chance to form organic seat shells that conform to the body's shape. The enduring forms and quality construction make the Molded Plastic Chairs - available here with a classic Eames wire base - comfortable, durable performers....New materials, especially those that held promise for doing more with less, fascinated Charles and Ray Eames throughout their careers. Their fascination led to inventive modern furniture, such as the Molded Plastic Chair. Designed in 1948, it was the first plastic chair to be mass produced....The current models look exactly the same as the originals. They remain un-upholstered, in keeping with the Eameses requirement that materials be expressed honestly and un-self consciously. In fact, these were the first one-piece plastic chairs to be left uncovered    At the same time, the chairs are better than ever. For example, the shell is now manufactured using more environmentally friendly, high-impact plastic.
description.967.0: English garden pavilions are echoed in the decor and elegant style of the Regeant Collection. Leather wrapped rattan.
description.969.0: Refined elegance is exemplified in the design of the Marston Collection.
description.971.0: Lend a stunning and graceful touch to your home interiors with the Sunset Trading Brookdale Napoleon Side Chair. The dining room is well suited for country or cottage home decors. The simple yet classic design enhances the beauty of the chair.The Brookdale Napoleon Side Chair by Sunset Trading has an Asian hardwood construction that ensures excellent quality and durability. The chair is available in a dual tone wheat and pecan finish with beautiful distressed detailing. The fine and lustrous design adds enchanting charm to your room interiors and elevates its look. The chair complements most dining tables and provide with an extra seating place in your kitchen or dining room. The four legs provide stability to the chair and the curved back makes it more comfortable. This graceful dining chair will seamlessly blend into your living room or dining room and add a blush of elegance to your decor.  The side chair is a part of the Brookdale collection by Sunset Trading. It is easy to care for and can be wiped clean with a damp cloth. The perfect size, light weight, and compact design make this chair handy and can be carried anywhere you go.
description.973.0: A classic form made modern with vivid orange, Finchum Designer Dining Chair is an unexpected pop of color for a chic dining room. Taking its inspiration from dowel-slatted chairs, this updated version is made instead with molded plastic. The Finchum Chair features non-marking feet to protect sensitive flooring from scratches. This design is fully stackable. To clean, wipe with a damp cloth.
description.977.0: Harry Bertoia's delicately industrial Side Chair is among the most recognized achievements of mid-century modern design. Like Saarinen and Mies, Bertoia found sublime grace in an industrial material, elevating it beyond its normal utility into a work of art.
description.982.0: Enhance the luxury of your home with furniture that is as alluring as it is durable. Marrying teakwood with master craftsmanship, the results are an elegant, trendy and unique touch to your interior design concept.
description.983.0: Sophisticated Rego chair will enhance any room setting.
description.984.0: The Mid-Century Eiffel dining chair features a clean, simple form sculpted in hand laid fiberglass. The seat is supported by solid wood Eiffel legs with a black coated steel assembly. In this design, different colors are available.
description.986.0: Cottage Cove creates a warm and welcoming feeling with its relaxed gracious styling. The maple finish with white hang up creates a character of its own for this group. The shaped spindle back chairs feature khaki linen upholstery and turned legs.
description.987.0: The Cosmopolitan Collection brings with it a sophisticated edge and flair. This contemporary group offers a variety of tables, chairs, gathering tables, and stools to fit the most exquisite taste.
description.988.0: La Dolce Vita. Inspired by photos found in an abandoned Italian palazzo, the set of Fabrizio side chairs is a modern spin on old world style. Their slightly curved rattan backs frame a brown patterned cushion sitting atop classically carved mahogany legs.
description.989.0: Ride the pathways of inspiration with the Skate Dining Chair. Skate is made of solid elm wood, and comes with non-marking plastic foot glides. Coated with a wood grain polyurethane finish, Skate does well in kitchens, dining rooms, cafes and restaurant seating areas.
description.99.0: The Woodbridge Home Designs Ohana Side Chair (Set of 2) is a blend of style and functionality. The double helix pattern on the backrest of this chair is its distinguishing design feature. The seat of the chair has a flat and smooth surface that offers firm support. The legs of this chair afford it great balance. Available in multiple finishes the Ohana Side Chair (Set of 2) by Woodbridge Home Designs looks great in different contemporary interior schemes. A premium wooden construction imparts strength and sturdiness. Made from non-toxic materials the chair is safe to use in homes with children. The eco-friendly nature of this chair makes minimal impact on the environment.
description.991.0: The International Concepts Unfinished Wood Arrowback Side Chair is an ideal option to pair with your elegant dining table. Beautifully styled, this side chair is versatile enough to be used with a patio table or any informal dining setup. Simple and robust, this chair can be easily accommodated in a small area along with the table. The Unfinished Wood Arrowback Side Chair by International Concepts is constructed from high-quality parawood to ensure unrivaled toughness and durability. It has a rustic unfinished surface, which not only looks raw and edgy, but also blends well with cottage and country decors. Featuring a spacious seating area, this chair is designed to offer maximum comfort. The Unfinished Wood Arrowback Side Chair comes with a Windsor back, which is planted into the seat, for favorable lower back support. This side chair from the house of International Concepts stands on four plain legs that provide a wobble-free and anti-slip base. It has bar stretchers connecting all the legs for added longevity and sturdiness. It can be easily assembled with the help of simple tools and requires cleaning with a soft, dry cloth to keep away dust and grime.
description.992.0: Handsome bonded leather chair with nickel nailheads (double row on the back), hardwood framing, and subtle seat and back profiling.
description.993.0: Combining contemporary and transitional elements, this dining chair is attractively designed with a soft wing back and accented with large silver nailhead. Stocked with CA foam.
description.995.0: A great option to keep by your fireplace, the Universal Furniture Villa Cortina Arm Chair (Set of 2) has a quintessential traditional style that is hard to miss. It can also be placed in your study room or bedroom to curl up enjoy a book. The Villa Cortina Arm Chair (Set of 2) from Universal Furniture is constructed from premium-quality hardwoods, for unrivaled strength and durability. It is further accentuated with laurel burl and hedguia borders that add an old-world charm to these chairs. This chair set has a charming cherry finish, which seamlessly blends with most decors. The Villa Cortina Arm Chair has brass tacking, and is offered in a range of upholstery varieties to choose from. It has a solid back and delicately curved arms, which facilitate in maintaining a good posture while sitting. This chair stands on four gently curved legs for optimum balance and support on the floor. The Villa Cortina Arm Chair from the house of Universal Furniture is low on maintenance, and can be easily cleaned with a soft, dry cloth.

Charles and Ray Eames adapted molding techniques developed during World War II to mass produce this classic design. Available in side and armchair versions, Today's Molded Plastic Chairs are true to the originals and are fully authentic, with updated materials to meet environmental requirements.     Charles and Ray Eames, always interested in new materials, saw in plastic the chance to form organic seat shells that conform to the body's shape. The enduring forms and quality construction make the Molded Plastic Chairs - available here with a classic Eames wire base - comfortable, durable performers.    The Design:      New materials, especially those that held promise for doing more with less, fascinated Charles and Ray Eames throughout their careers. Their fascination led to inventive modern furniture, such as the Molded Plastic Chair. Designed in 1948, it was the first plastic chair to be mass produced, The current models look exactly the same as the originals. They remain unupholstered, in keeping with the Eameses requirement that materials be expressed honestly and unselfconsciously. In fact, these were the first one-piece plastic chairs to be left uncovered    At the same time, the chairs are better than ever. For example, the shell is now manufactured using more environmentally friendly, high-impact plastic

Features at a Glance: Clean, simple form sculpted to fit the body
Features at a Glance: First presented at the Museum of Modern Art in 1948, the chairs have achieved a pervasive presence that proves the staying power of good design

Features at a Glance: Classic Eames Dowel-Leg Base
Smart Construction: Durable design, even in public spaces

Philippe Starck and Eugeni Quitllet pay homage to three different midcentury modern masters in one sleek, versatile indoor-outdoor seat. The Masters Chair (2010) weaves together the back silhouettes of Jacobsen's Series 7Chair, the Eameses' Molded Plastic Chair and Saarinen's Tulip Armchair to create something entirely new. Lightweight and durable, the Masters Chair has a wide, roomy seat, while the back rest allows you to feel supported on a historic level as it echoes the lines of the very first ergonomic innovators. The iconoclastic Starck has been working with Kartell since the 1980s, mixing the company's desire to develop eco-friendly, contemporary plastic furniture with the designer's unmistakably edgy and innovative style. Stackable up to four high. Made in Italy. The Masters chair is a powerful tribute to the three symbolic chairs, re-read and re-interpreted by the creative genius of Starck. The "Series 7" by Arne Jacobsen, the "Tulip Armchair" by Eero Saarinen and the "Eiffel Chair" by Charles Eames interweave their unmistakable silhouettes into a sinuous hybrid giving life to a fusion of original and engaging styles. On its four slim legs, the Masters chair is roomy and comfy. The special finish on the chair makes it feel sensual and velvety to the touch. The back of the chair is naturally its most distinctive feature, characterised by the fullness and empty spaces created by the curvaceous criss-crossing lines of three different backs which descend to meet at the seat edge. The Masters is light, practical and can be stacked and used outdoors as well. The Masters chair was honoured with the prestigious "2010 Good Design Award" presented by the Chicago Athenaeum - Museum of Architecture and Design.

Features

Material: Modified batch-dyed polypropylene

description_all.966.0:
Charles and Ray Eames adapted molding techniques developed during World War II to mass produce this classic design. Today's Molded Plastic Chairs are true to the originals and are fully authentic, with updated materials to meet environmental requirements. Charles and Ray Eames, always interested in new materials, saw in plastic the chance to form organic seat shells that conform to the body's shape. The enduring forms and quality construction make the Molded Plastic Chairs - available here with a classic Eames wire base - comfortable, durable performers....New materials, especially those that held promise for doing more with less, fascinated Charles and Ray Eames throughout their careers. Their fascination led to inventive modern furniture, such as the Molded Plastic Chair. Designed in 1948, it was the first plastic chair to be mass produced....The current models look exactly the same as the originals. They remain un-upholstered, in keeping with the Eameses requirement that materials be expressed honestly and un-self consciously. In fact, these were the first one-piece plastic chairs to be left uncovered    At the same time, the chairs are better than ever. For example, the shell is now manufactured using more environmentally friendly, high-impact plastic.

Features

Organic shape
Clean, simple form sculpted to fit the body
First presented at the Museum of Modern Art in 1948, the chairs have achieved a pervasive presence that proves the staying power of good design

A great option to keep by your fireplace, the Universal Furniture Villa Cortina Arm Chair (Set of 2) has a quintessential traditional style that is hard to miss. Featuring beautiful curves and clean cuts, this armchair can also be paired with a small rustic table to enjoy your evening snacks or coffee. It can also be placed in your study room or bedroom to curl up enjoy a book. The Villa Cortina Arm Chair (Set of 2) from Universal Furniture is constructed from premium-quality hardwoods, for unrivaled strength and durability. It is further accentuated with laurel burl and hedguia borders that add an old-world charm to these chairs. This chair set has a charming cherry finish, which seamlessly blends with most decors. The Villa Cortina Arm Chair has brass tacking, and is offered in a range of upholstery varieties to choose from. It has a solid back and delicately curved arms, which facilitate in maintaining a good posture while sitting. This chair stands on four gently curved legs for optimum balance and support on the floor. The Villa Cortina Arm Chair from the house of Universal Furniture is low on maintenance, and can be easily cleaned with a soft, dry cloth.

Features

Hardwoods with laurel burl and hedguia borders and cherry veneer
Fully upholstered with brass tacking
Chair fabric: 73% Rayon, 27% polyester
